chinchilla my boyfriend's bday is coming up and i know he really wants a ferret but they r illegal in california so that would be hard to get so i was wondering of a chinchilla would that b a good idea they r both rodents actually ferrets are not rodents and the chinchilla's classification as a rodent is currently contested however chinchillas make very nice pets they are very friendly and like being paid attention to and petted provided you spend some time taming them and letting them get used to you they need a nice big cage and possibly a wheel and weekly dust baths www martinscages com has good chinchilla cages and you can get chinchilla bath dust and bath houses at petsmart or petco you can also get a healthy well socialized chinchilla through a breeder for a lot less than it costs to buy one at a petstore try google to do a search for chinchilla breeders in california i know there are quite a few Chinchilla Ferret Hamster People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals Pet Pet skunk Guinea pig Cat Rodent Degu Rabbit Hunting Kim Possible Domestic rabbit Gaia Online Dog The Amazing Maurice and his Educated Rodents Falconry Exotic pet Rat Canary Garfield Pet Shop Boys The Sims The Pet Sounds Sessions One Piece minor characters Kart racing Cheetah Creatures in Bionicle Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography The Beach Boys The Apprentice 2 Weebl's cartoons Professional wrestling match types Final Fantasy XI Ai Yori Aoshi Pets.com Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Chicken Neopets Rabies Capital accumulation Legal research Social rule Discus (fish) Monster Rancher monsters RuneScape quests Caviomorpha Monkey Health insurance W.I.T.C.H. Microeconomics Pig Externality Bath Inception of Darwin's theory Development of Darwin's theory Euphemism Maltese tiger American Pit Bull Terrier Brian Wilson Mustelidae House Mouse Keeshond Ron and Fez Great Depression Pet store Search engine optimization Sin City Havanese SpongeBob SquarePants Irish Wolfhound The Ersatz Elevator Poker 